ce:section.ce:para:
The high volatile A bituminous Blue Gem coal (CS-1) is, aside from its geochemistry (discussed in the Introduction and, specifically for this sample, shown in Table 1
                        ), petrographically similar to many other eastern Kentucky coals (Table 2
                        ). It has nearly 80% vitrinite group macerals, with the balance being nearly equal amounts of inertinite and liptinite; examples of the maceral assemblages are shown on Fig. 1
                        .
